<subSubSection id="788C652AC851537B9A8ECB75FC6824F8" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="302936A1C851537B9A8ECB75FED62440" blockId="3.[160,1155,853,983]" box="[160,285,853,879]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="02E2EAB3C851537B9A8ECB75FED62440" bold="true" box="[160,285,853,879]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302936A1C851537B9A8ECB59FC6824F8" blockId="3.[160,1155,853,983]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
The species is named after Dra Karla Magalhães Campião, Department of Zoology, Federal University of 
<collectingRegion id="F252F843C851537B9B18CBBBFE49249B" box="[310,386,923,948]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Paraná</collectingRegion>
(UFPR), 
<collectingRegion id="F252F843C851537B9BCDCBBBFDF9249B" box="[483,562,923,948]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="48817631C851537B9813CBBBFDB7249B" box="[573,636,923,948]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, for her significant contribution to the knowledge of ecology and parasitism of Brazilian amphibians and reptiles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="788C652AC85153709A8ECC3CFD1E27C2" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="description">
<paragraph id="302936A1C851537B9A8ECC3CFEE02319" blockId="3.[160,299,1052,1078]" box="[160,299,1052,1078]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<heading id="6B6181CDC851537B9A8ECC3CFEE02319" bold="true" box="[160,299,1052,1078]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" reason="3">
<emphasis id="02E2EAB3C851537B9A8ECC3CFEE02319" bold="true" box="[160,299,1052,1078]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302936A1C851537B9A8ECC70FF372345" blockId="3.[160,1155,1104,1304]" box="[160,252,1104,1130]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="02E2EAB3C851537B9A8ECC70FF372345" bold="true" box="[160,252,1104,1130]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">General</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302936A1C851537B9A8ECC54FEB82237" blockId="3.[160,1155,1104,1304]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Small cylindrical nematodes, sexually dimorphic, males approximately one-third length of female. Lateral alae present in males, absent in females. Caudal alae absent in males (Figuere 3(a)). Anterior extremity tapered, mouth opening triangular with three simple lips, a pair of amphids located on ventrolateral lips, and absent sessile papillae in both sexes (
<figureCitation id="A8AD2A24C851537B9AC5CCDFFE822237" box="[235,329,1279,1304]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1153,1176]" captionTargetBox="[169,1141,152,1115]" captionTargetId="figure-157@5.[163,1153,142,1121]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Scanning electron microscope images of Skrjabinodon campiaoae sp. nov. (a) Male, anterior end view (arrow: lateral ala); (b) detail of anterior end of mouth and amphids (arrows); (c) female posterior end." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456956/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(b)).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302936A1C851537B9A8ECD6CFE452249" blockId="3.[160,1156,1356,1728]" box="[160,398,1356,1382]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="02E2EAB3C851537B9A8ECD6CFE452249" bold="true" box="[160,398,1356,1382]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Male (
<specimenCount id="2690FD28C851537B9AC5CD6CFE4E2249" box="[235,389,1356,1382]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="generic" typeStatus="holotype">one holotype</specimenCount>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="302936A1C851537B9A8ECD4FFDDF21EF" blockId="3.[160,1156,1356,1728]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Length (excluding tail filament) 1036 ± 143 µm (896−1161); width at level of excretory pore 101 ± 25 (75−134); cuticle with distinct transverse pseudo-annulations; lateral alae starting at level of nerve ring and disappearing at level of first ventral pair of precloacal papillae; longitudinal striations absent; oesophagus length 210 ± 30 (165−227): corpus length 155 ± 26 (116−174); isthmus length 9; bulb length 57 ± 7 (46−63); bulb width 63 ± 11 (47−70); nerve ring 60 ± 5 (54−64) and excretory pore 306 from anterior end, respectively; spicule absent; smooth cloacal lips; caudal alae absent; four pairs of mammiliform papillae: one precloacal ventrally directed, two postcloacal ventrally directed, and one at base of filament tail (
<figureCitation id="A8AD2A24C851537B9829CEA5FDA521B1" box="[519,622,1669,1694]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1625,1648]" captionTargetBox="[167,1138,146,1591]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[163,1153,142,1594]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Skrjabinodon campiaoae sp. nov. (a) Female,total length; (b) female, anterior end; (c) female, en face view; (d) female, posterior end, lateral view; (e) egg; (f) male, total length; (g) male, posterior end, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456954" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456954/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Figures 2</figureCitation>
(g) and 4(b)). Tail filament 216 ± 70 (117−275) in length, with 3–9 spines (
<tableCitation id="7D14031AC851537B9B9BCE87FDCC21EF" box="[437,519,1703,1728]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="7.[133,189,607,630]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Table 1. Comparative measurements (in µm, with mean followed by the range) of Neotropical species of the genus Skrjabinodon." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/64E96629C855537F9AABCA7FFA472559" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" tableUuid="64E96629C855537F9AABCA7FFA472559">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
